'''Paul Taylor''' is Professor Emeritus of International Relations at the [[London School of Economics and Political Science]]. His main areas of expertise are European integration and international organisations.<ref>{{cite web|title=Professor Emeritus Paul Taylor|url=http://www.lse.ac.uk/researchandexpertise/experts/profile.aspx?KeyValue=p.taylor%40lse.ac.uk|website=The London School of Economics and Political Science|accessdate=20 October 2017}}</ref> From 2001 to 2004 he was Director of the European Institute at the same institution.<ref>{{cite book|title=The end of European integration: anti-Europeanism examined|date=2008|publisher=Routledge|location=Abingdon, UK|isbn=9780415431064}}</ref>
==Publications== *Taylor, P. (2010). The careless state: Wealth and welfare in Britain today. Bloomsbury. *Taylor, P. (2008). The end of European integration: Anti-Europeanism examined. Routledge. *Taylor, P. (2005). International organization in the age of globalization. Continuum. *Taylor, P. (1996). The European Union in the 1990s. Oxford University Press. *Taylor, P. (1993). Taylor, Paul (1993) International organization in the modern world: the regional and the global pattern. Pinter. *Taylor, P. (1983). The limits of European integration. Croom Helm.
